clearing a bit:clearing a bit indicates if the given position is 1 then it changes to 0 if it is 0 then it is unchanged 
clear a bit : '&'
set a bit :'|'
toggle a bit:'^'

#include <stdio.h
int main()
{
    int n=8,pos=2;
    int res=(n&~(1<<pos-1));
    printf("clearing a bit at particular position:%d",res);
    return 0;
}
